The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and college students at the College of Southern Nevada. Harris discusses the importance of voting, the fight for gun violence prevention, reproductive rights, LGBTQ+ rights, and the climate crisis. She emphasizes the need for unity, coalition-building, and the power of the people to bring about change. Harris also shares some of her accomplishments, such as capping the cost of insulin for seniors and investing in climate change initiatives. She encourages the students to be leaders and to use their voices to make a difference.